    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00288.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office<ptr
                            target="loc.07221_n1"/><lb/>ASYLUM FOR THE INSANE<lb/>LONDON.<lb/>
                        ONTARIO<lb/>London, Ont.,</name>
                    <date when="1888-08-10" rend="right"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>10 Aug
                            <handShift rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your card of 8th to hand this morning. Dr. Harkness<ptr target="n4278"/> came
                yesterday afternoon, he will make a short visit, 5 or 6 days, with me&#8212;he is
                well. The weather continues pleasant here not at all unpleasantly hot. There is
                nothing special stirring. I should like to hear that you are gaining
                strength&#8212;I do not hear that&#8212;how is it? Nothing back from Willy Gurd<ptr
                target="n4284"/>&#8212;I still hope I may see you sometime next month but
                nothing certain about it</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>Your friend</salute>
                <signed rend="right">RM Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
